OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F416A1756472760
OL,3,CDrink-driver who crashed into tree on
OL,4,Cnight out killing passenger, sentenced
OL,6,F"This has been a tragic case for all
OL,7,Finvolved. Our investigation shows that
OL,8,Fthe cause of the collision was due to
OL,9,Fthe irresponsible actions of the
OL,10,Fdriver in consuming alcohol and having
OL,11,Flittle to no regard for the safety of
OL,12,Fhis passenger, furthermore failing to
OL,13,Fheed the warning of his passengers to
OL,14,Fslow down.
OL,16,F"The message is clear, never get
OL,17,Fbehind the wheel of a vehicle after
OL,18,Fdrinking alcohol and if you are a
OL,19,Fpassenger, don't be afraid to refuse a
OL,20,Flift."
